title: Medium-strength quake hits near Philippine island
text:
May 5, 2018 / 6:38 AM / in 11 hours Medium-strength quake hits near Philippine island Reuters Staff 1 Min Read
(Reuters) - A 6.1 magnitude earthquake struck in the Philippines on Saturday, the U.S. Geological Survey said.
There were no immediate reports of casualties or damage from the quake, which hit at a depth of 30 km (18 miles), about 50 km north-northwest of Pandan, on the island of Catanduanes.
USGS earlier put the quake at a strength of 6.4. Reporting by Nick Macfie
